{{BLP refimprove|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = His Excellency | name = Alex Vadakumthala | title = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kannur|Bishop of Kannur]] | image = <!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Alex Vadakumthala.jpg|thumb|right|Bishop Alex Vadakumthala]] --> | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kannur|Kannur Diocese]] | appointed = 1 February 2014 | term = 2014–present | predecessor = Varghese Chakkalakal | successor = | ordination = 19 December 1984 | ordained_by = | consecration = 23 March 2014 | consecrated_by = [[Salvatore Pennacchio]] | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Panagad]], [[Kerala]], [[India]] | death_date = | death_place = | previous_post = Vicar General }}
Bishop Dr. '''Alex Vadakumthala''' was ordained as Priest on December 19, 1984. He served as the Vicar General of the Archdiocese of Verapoly. He was appointed as Bishop of Kannur on 1 February 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mattersindia.com/pope-francis-appoints-kannur-bishop/|title=Pope Francis appoints Kannur bishop |publisher=Matters India|date=2014-02-01|accessdate=2014-02-15}}</ref> He has served as the Executive Secretary of the CBCI Commission for Health Care. He had also served as the Project Director, Constant Lievens National Academy of Healy Sciences, Ranchi (CBCIs - Ambitious Medical College and Hospital Project for North India).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.persecution.in/content/very-rev-msgr-alex-vadakumthala-appointed-new-bishop-kannur |title=Archived copy |access-date=14 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140214043841/http://www.persecution.in/content/very-rev-msgr-alex-vadakumthala-appointed-new-bishop-kannur |archive-date=14 February 2014 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
