'''The Anointed King / Beili Wang''' (被立王) is a Christian [[cult]] of [[Christian]] origin in the [[People's Republic of China]], which possibly had more than 100,000 members at its peak. It emphasizes [[Christian eschatology|eschatology]] and is in favour of a Christian empire. Founded in [[Anhui]] in 1987 or 1988, It was present in Anhui, [[Hunan]], [[Guangdong]] and possibly other areas (Including [[Taiwan]] and [[Southeast Asia]]). Its founder, Wu Yangming (吴扬明), formerly of [[The Shouters]], took the title ''Beili Wang''. Beili Wang has been banned in the People's Republic of China since 1995, and Wu was [[executed]] for [[rape]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnfxj.org/Html/xiejiaocn/2007-5/7/114221673.html|publisher=中国反邪教网|script-title=zh:被立王|date=2007-05-07|language=zh|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510051352/http://www.cnfxj.org/Html/xiejiaocn/2007-5/7/114221673.html|archivedate=2012-05-10|df=}}</ref>

