'''Christotokos''' is the Greek title of [[Mary (mother of Jesus)|Mary]], the mother of [[Jesus]] used historically by [[First Council of Ephesus|non-Ephesians]] followers of the [[Church of the East]]. Its literal English translations include ''Christ-bearer'' and ''the one who gives birth to Christ''. Less literal translations include ''Mother of Christ''.<ref>{{cite book | title=Learning Theology With the Church Fathers | publisher=InterVarsity Press | author=Hall, Christopher Alan | year=2002 | pages=8–9 | isbn=9780830826865 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z0Fq7Rk7howC&pg=PA8}}</ref>
