{{Infobox Organization |name= Leather & Grace |image= |size= |caption= |abbreviation = L&G |formation= 2011 |founder= [[Desmond Ravenstone]] |extinction= |type= {{hlist | [[Religious organization]] | [[BDSM]]/[[kink (sexual)|kink]]}} |purpose= To engage in educational and advocacy work for "kink-oriented" [[Unitarian Universalism|Unitarian Universalists]] within the denomination |headquarters = |location= United States |leader_title= Moderator |leader_name= [[Desmond Ravenstone]] |affiliations = [[National Coalition for Sexual Freedom]] |membership= |language= |num_staff= |budget= |website= {{official URL}} }}
'''Leather & Grace''' ('''L&G''') is an organization of [[Unitarian Universalism|Unitarian Universalists]] who identify with or support the [[BDSM]]/[[kink (sexual)|kink]] community. Founded in 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://leatherandgrace.wordpress.com/an-organization-for-uu-kinksters/ |title=Leather & Grace website: L&G's Story }}</ref> L&G is a member of the [[National Coalition for Sexual Freedom]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ncsfreedom.org/who-we-are/coalition-partners.html |title=NCSF: Who We Are: Coalition Partners }}</ref> and engages in educational and advocacy work for "kink-oriented" UUs within the denomination.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uua.org/sites/live-new.uua.org/files/documents/boardtrustees/130420_minutes.pdf |title=Minutes of UUA Board of Trustees meeting, April 20-21, 2013 |publisher=UUA }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://huffingtonpost.com/amy-shiner/spirituality-meet-leather_b_1227772.html |title="Spirituality Meets Leather" by Amy Shiner |publisher=Huffington Post |date=January 23, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://revrost.blogspot.com/2015/2/so-i-say-if-you-are-burning-burn-if-you_26.html |title=sUbteXt: "So I say, if you are burning, burn ..." |publisher=Nori J. Rost |date=February 26, 2015 }}</ref> The organization's efforts are coordinated by an elected steering committee, which appoints and oversees specialized committees (educational outreach, crisis response, etc.) and local affiliates. The current Moderator is [[Desmond Ravenstone]], a lay leader at the [[Arlington Street Church]] in [[Boston, Massachusetts]].
Their logo combines a red [[flaming chalice]] with the stripes of the [[Leather Pride flag]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://leatherandgrace.wordpress.com/an-organization-for-uu-kinksters/|title=Leather & Grace: L&G's Story}}</ref>
