A '''Pontifical Legate''' is a personal representative of the [[Pope]].
Specifically, this title is used for: * the formal title of the Cardinal or (Arch)bishop appointed to represent the Holy See in the administration of one or more [[Major basilica#Papal basilicas|Papal]] [[minor basilica]](s), notably: ** the [[Pontifical Legation for the Basilicas of Saint Francis and Saint Mary of the Angels in Assisi]] (or until 2006, its precursor only for the [[Basilica of Saint Francis of Assisi]]) * a generic synonym for any (usually diplomatic) [[papal legate]]
