'''Sadhabhisekam''' is one of the religious [[Ceremony|ceremonies]] done in [[Hinduism]].  It is one of the formal ceremonies (and can be called a duty to all children) done by the children to their parents, when the father reaches the age of 80.

The same preparation done for every [[marriage]] will be done for this also, like invitation preparation, food arrangements, booking of hall for guests.

